                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.011/105: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-12T15:00:00-05:45"
                            >May 12, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. My telegram No. 65, April 27, 3 p.m. The Nicaraguan Congress has recessed
                    until May 31, 1932. It seems that this recess was brought about by President
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJM2">Moncada</persName>. The matter of constitutional
                    reform is still pending in the Congress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HME1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
